Tucson knew that fuel reserves needed to be replenished.  Lucky for him he 
had emergency reserves subspaced within his draconic body.  He opens up the 
left front haunch compartment and reveals a line of canisters.

&quot; I&#39;m sure many of you need fuel.  Help yourselves but try to consider 
others who are Also in need of refueling.&quot; I have a second reserve on my 
right side.&quot;

While with Waspinator, Straight Shot giggles with delight.  She loved a 
little thrill seeking and being almost dropped was actually exciting to her.

&quot; That&#39;s okay, it was actually kinda fun.  I&#39;ve never had the opportunity to 
fly and I&#39;m enjoying it.&quot;

She transforms into her robot mode and catches hold to Waspinator&#39;s spindly 
legs, keeping a sure but gentile grip on it.  She keeps her beacon on track 
mode while flying with what could very well be an evolving friendship.  She 
looks up to Waspinator with a smile and a thumbs up.

&quot; We&#39;re still on track, and my beacon is  rapidly flashing.  We must be 
getting close.&quot;

She now swings herself up onto his back, carefully minding his wings.  She 
proves to be a very light passenger as she rides contently on the Predacon&#39;s 
back.

&quot;I never thought that I would ever make friends among enemies but, I think I 
just did.  Nobody has ta know anything except for us.   What&#39;d ya say? 
Friends?  I promise never ta tell Leo or Rodimus.  Tucson will understand 
but I don&#39;t think the other two will.&quot;

She couldn&#39;t exactly tell what was happening to her but whatever it was, 
certainly didn&#39;t bother her in the least.

